1.body aches, fever (flu type symptoms)
2. Cold symptoms(headache )
3. Bronchitis / Sinus Infection
Its takes a long time to get through the last 2 symptoms.
I would just stay away from the elderly, and if you're starting to come down with something think about others. Cover your coughs sneezes etc.

snippet.textDisplay: Maybe air pollution could be a factor? China and Italy have high pollution. About a quarter of Italy's population smokes. I lived in Arkansas for 6 years, smoking in public was way too common. It was disturbing. Even the non smokers smelled like smoke. I know this has a lasting effect on your health, particularly your lungs. Same thing could apply to pollution exposure. Also, tonsils? Do these healthy people who developed severe coronavirus symptoms have their tonsils? Tonsils are your pharmacy. Without them your body has an even harder time figuring out how to fight bugs. And lastly, vaccines. What is the history of their vaccines? Viruses don't want to kill you, they want to survive and coexist with their host. Some vaccines and pharmaceuticals stifle our ability to strengthen our immune system. Idk, whatever the cause may be, one thing is for sure, humans are the deadliest virus. We need nature to survive and thrive. Big cities are for robots. We will never evolve to withstand any sort of pollution.
